[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A Provider provides a connection to the blockchain, which can be used to query its current state, simulate execution and send transactions to update the state.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] It is one of the most fundamental components of interacting with a blockchain application, and there are many ways to connect, such as over HTTP, WebSockets or injected providers such as MetaMask.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] numeric value - specifies the block height, where the genesis block is block 0; many operations accept a negative value which indicates the block number should be deducted from the most recent block.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A numeric value may be a number, bigint, or a decimal of hex string.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] blockhash - specifies a specific block by its blockhash; this allows potentially orphaned blocks to be specifed, without ambiguity, but many backends do not support this for some operations.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The possible additional events dispatched when using the "debug" event on a BrowserProvider.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The gas cost parameters for a GasCostPlugin.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] An Orphan Filter allows detecting when an orphan block has resulted in dropping a block or transaction or has resulted in transactions changing order.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A ProviderEvent provides the types of events that can be subscribed to on a Provider.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] "block" - calls the listener with the current block number on each new block.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] "error" - calls the listener on each async error that occurs during the event loop, with the error.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] "debug" - calls the listener on debug events, which can be used to troubleshoot network errors, provider problems, etc.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] transaction hash - calls the listener on each block after the transaction has been mined; generally .once is more appropriate for this event.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Array - calls the listener on each log that matches the filter.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A TopicFilter provides a struture to define bloom-filter queries.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Each field that is null matches any value, a field that is a string must match exactly that value and array is effectively an OR-ed set, where any one of those values must match.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A function which can be used to re-create a WebSocket connection on disconnect.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Returns a copy of req with all properties coerced to their strict types.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] If network is a WebSocketLike or string that begins with "ws:" or "wss:", a WebSocketProvider is returned backed by that WebSocket or URL.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] If network is a string that begins with "HTTP:" or "HTTPS:", a JsonRpcProvider is returned connected to that URL.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Otherwise, a default provider is created backed by well-known public Web3 backends (such as INFURA) using community-provided API keys.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The options allows specifying custom API keys per backend (setting an API key to "-" will omit that provider) and options.exclusive can be set to either a backend name or and array of backend names, which will whitelist only those backends.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A Block represents the data associated with a full block on Ethereum.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The base fee per gas that all transactions in this block were charged.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] This adjusts after each block, depending on how congested the network is.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The total amount of blob gas consumed by the transactions within the block.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] On legacy networks, this is the proof-of-work target required for a block to meet the protocol rules to be included.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] On modern networks, this is a random number arrived at using randao. @TODO: Find links?
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The running total of blob gas consumed in excess of the target, prior to the block.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Any extra data the validator wished to include.
