[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] On legacy networks, this is the random number inserted which permitted the difficulty target to be reached.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The block number, sometimes called the block height.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] This is a sequential number that is one higher than the parent block.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The hash tree root of the parent beacon block for the given execution block.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Returns the complete transactions, in the order they were executed within the block.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] This is only available for blocks which prefetched transactions, by passing true to prefetchTxs into provider.getBlock.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The latest RANDAO mix of the post beacon state of the previous block.
