[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] An EventFilter allows efficiently filtering logs (also known as events) using bloom filters included within blocks.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A FeeData wraps all the fee-related values associated with the network.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The base fee per gas is defined by the network and based on congestion, increasing the cost during times of heavy load and lowering when less busy.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The actual fee per gas will be the base fee for the block and the priority fee, up to the max fee per gas.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The additional amout to pay per gas to encourage a validator to include the transaction.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The purpose of this is to compensate the validator for the adjusted risk for including a given transaction.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Creates a new FeeData for gasPrice, maxFeePerGas and maxPriorityFeePerGas.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A FeeDataNetworkPlugin allows a network to provide and alternate means to specify its fee data.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] For example, a network which does not support EIP-1559 may choose to use a Gas Station site to approximate the gas price.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The fee data function provided to the constructor.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The callback to use when computing the FeeData.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The URL to initialize the FetchRequest with in processFunc.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Creates a new FetchUrlFeeDataNetworkPlugin which will be used when computing the fee data for the network.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A Filter allows searching a specific range of blocks for mathcing logs.
