[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The end block for the filter (inclusive).
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A FilterByBlockHash allows searching a specific block for mathcing logs.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The blockhash of the specific block for the filter.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A GasCostPlugin allows a network to provide alternative values when computing the intrinsic gas required for a transaction.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The block number to treat these values as valid from.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] This allows a hardfork to have updated values included as well as mulutiple hardforks to be supported.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The fee per address in the EIP-2930 access list.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The fee per storage key in the EIP-2930 access list.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Creates a new GasCostPlugin from effectiveBlock until the latest block or another GasCostPlugin supercedes that block number, with the associated costs.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] An IpcSocketProvider connects over an IPC socket on the host which provides fast access to the node, but requires the node and the script run on the same machine.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] A Log in Ethereum represents an event that has been included in a transaction using the LOG* opcodes, which are most commonly used by Solidity's emit for announcing events.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The address of the contract that emitted this log.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The block hash of the block this log occurred in.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The block number of the block this log occurred in.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] It is preferred to use the block.hash when fetching the related Block, since in the case of an orphaned block, the block at that height may have changed.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The data included in this log when it was emitted.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The index within the block this log occurred at.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] This is generally not useful to developers, but can be used with the various roots to proof inclusion within a block.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The provider connected to the log used to fetch additional details if necessary.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] If the Log represents a block that was removed due to an orphaned block, this will be true.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] This can only happen within an orphan event listener.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The indexed topics included in this log when it was emitted.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] All topics are included in the bloom filters, so they can be efficiently filtered using the provider.getLogs method.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The transaction hash of the transaction this log occurred in.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Use the log.getTransaction to get the TransactionResponse.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The index within the transaction of this log.
