[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Signs an EIP-191 prefixed personal message.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] If the message is a string, it is signed as UTF-8 encoded bytes.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] It is not interpretted as a BytesLike; so the string "0x1234" is signed as six characters, not two bytes.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] To sign that example as two bytes, the Uint8Array should be used (i.e. new Uint8Array([ 0x12, 0x34 ])).
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] Signs tx, returning the fully signed transaction.
