[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] It is implicitly computed from the transaction pre-image hash (as the digest) and the signature using ecrecover.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The maximum units of gas this transaction can consume.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] If execution exceeds this, the entries transaction is reverted and the sender is charged for the full amount, despite not state changes being made.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p01] The gas price can have various values, depending on the network.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p02] In modern networks, for transactions that are included this is the effective gas price (the fee per gas that was actually charged), while for transactions that have not been included yet is the maxFeePerGas.
[src:ethers-js/api-providers-p02] For legacy transactions, or transactions on legacy networks, this is the fee that will be charged per unit of gas the transaction consumes.
